<subSubSection pageId="36" pageNumber="37" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="36.[151,1437,470,749]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,470,497]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Corallum monopodial and pinnulate, unattached, with hook-like holdfast for support in soft sediments. Pinnules simple, bilateral and alternate. Spines simple, triangular, compressed. Polyps 
<quantity box="[1122,1215,507,534]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" unit="mm" value="4.5" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="3.0">3â€“6 mm</quantity>
in transverse diameter (
<bibRefCitation author="Opresko, D. M." box="[208,379,543,569]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" pagination="411 - 442" refId="ref48859" refString="Opresko, D. M. (2002) Revision of the Antipatharia (Cnidaria: Anthozoa). Part II. Schizopathidae. Zoologische Mededelingen, 76, 411 - 442." type="journal article" year="2002">Opresko, 2002</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="36" pageNumber="37" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="36.[151,1437,470,749]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,579,605]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Remarks.</emphasis>
The genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Brook, 1889" authorityName="Brook" authorityYear="1889" box="[453,752,579,605]" class="Anthozoa" family="Schizopathidae" genus="Schizopathes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Antipatharia" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[453,599,579,605]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Schizopathes</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Brook, G." box="[609,752,579,605]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" refId="ref46539" refString="Brook, G. (1889) Report on the Antipatharia collected by HMS Challenger during the years 1873 - 1876. Zoology, 32, 1." type="journal volume" year="1889">Brook, 1889</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
is the only one, within the order, to harbor species that do not depend on hard substrates for fixation, presenting a modified hook for support in soft bottoms (Wagner, 2015; 
<bibRefCitation author="Opresko, D. M." box="[151,319,651,677]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" pagination="157 - 166" refId="ref48683" refString="Opresko, D. M. (1997) Review of the genus Schizopathes (Cnidaria: Antipatharia: Schizopathidae) with a description of a new species from the Indian Ocean. Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington, 110 (2), 157 - 166." type="journal article" year="1997">Opresko, 1997</bibRefCitation>
). Some species of the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Molodtsova &amp; Opresko" authorityYear="2017" box="[633,806,651,677]" class="Anthozoa" family="Schizopathidae" genus="Alternatipathes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Antipatharia" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[633,806,651,677]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Alternatipathes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and in particular, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Brook)" authorityName="Brook" baseAuthorityName="Brook" baseAuthorityYear="1889" box="[1010,1238,651,678]" class="Anthozoa" family="Schizopathidae" genus="Alternatipathes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Antipatharia" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="alternata">
<emphasis box="[1010,1027,652,678]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1040,1143,651,677]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">alternata</emphasis>
(Brook)
</taxonomicName>
are almost identical to species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Brook" authorityYear="1889" box="[338,484,687,713]" class="Anthozoa" family="Schizopathidae" genus="Schizopathes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Antipatharia" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[338,484,687,713]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Schizopathes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with the exception that they have a basal holdfast for attaching to hard substrates.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,754,722,749]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" type="distribution">
